.TH "audit_log_n_hex" 9 "audit_log_n_hex" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
audit_log_n_hex \- convert a buffer to hex and append it to the audit skb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" audit_log_n_hex
.BI "(struct audit_buffer *ab "  ","
.BI "const unsigned char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ab" 12
the audit_buffer
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to convert to hex
.IP "len" 12
length of \fIbuf\fP to be converted
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
No return value; failure to expand is silently ignored.

This function will take the passed buf and convert it into a string of
ascii hex digits. The new string is placed onto the skb.
